President Muhammadu Buhari has directed an investigation into the cause of the fire incident at the Oba Market in Benin Edo State. The President’s investigation order, he said, was in order to avoid the “horrific’’ situation in the future, while condoling with all those that were affected. President Buhari also called on local and federal authorities to provide assistance to victims of the fire incident. In a statement issued by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity Mallam Garba Shehu, the President said “our thoughts and prayers are with those who lost their shops and wares.’’ The Nation ABUJA - President Muhammadu Buhari has sympathised with the victims of the fire incidents in Sabon Gari Market, Kano State and Birnin Kebbi Central Market in Kebbi. According to a statement issued in Abuja on Saturday by Mallam Garba Shehu, Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity to the president,… March 27, 2016 In "Top Stories" Abuja -  President Muhammadu Buhari has sympathized with the victims of the fire incidents in Sabon Gari Market, Kano State and Birnin Kebbi Central Market in Kebbi. A statement issued in Abuja on Saturday by Mallam Garba Shehu, Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity to the president, said President… March 26, 2016 In "News" Kemerovo   -    President Vladimir Putin of Russia on Tuesday vowed that all those responsible for the tragic fire in a shopping mall in the Siberian city of Kemerovo would be punished. On Sunday, the major fire broke out in the Zimnyaya Vishnya (“Winter Cherry”) shopping center in Kemerovo. Russian Emergencies… March 27, 2018 In "Foreign"